 
<p>
Americans are suffering illness and death due to
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/may/02/us-surgeon-general-warning-loneliness">the level of
disconnection</a>
from other people.  The amount of direct contact
with other people has been decreasing since the 1970s.
<p>
The essay "Bowling Alone" took note of this development in 1995, but it
has continued since then.
<p>
By going to the store to buy things, you can have a little more social
contact with a variety of people &mdash; and you can <em>pay cash</em>
and resist surveillance capitalism.


<p>
 